|GKB-- Nwyfre -----------------------------------------------------|000

Nwyfre is the living current druids use for rituals and
invocations.  It replaces spell points for active druid
invocations.

There are four vessels:

  |CKBTellurian|000 - Darkwind, earth, roots, body, grove
  |CKBDaloan   |000 - Dailos, turmoil, flame, savagery
  |CKBMarken   |000 - Markas, healing, renewal, stability
  |CKBTekali   |000 - Tekal, knowledge, frost, sight, wind

Use |CKBnwyfre|000 to see all four vessels.  Each line shows a bar,
regen rate, cost modifier, and source world.
The Planet line shows where you are standing for nwyfre purposes.
Darkwind favors the Tellurian current; each moon favors its own
current and weakens the others.

|GKB-- Useful Commands -------------------------------------------|000

  |CKBnwyfre                |000 Show all vessels.
  |CKBnwyfre <current>      |000 Inspect one vessel.
  |CKBnwyfre active         |000 Show active rites, timers, and toggles.
  |CKBnwyfre moons          |000 Show current moon phases.
  |CKBnwyfre rituals        |000 List learned rituals.
  |CKBnwyfre learnable      |000 List rituals you can learn.
  |CKBnwyfre ritual <name>  |000 Inspect one ritual.

Rituals and celestial conditions change regen and cost.  Long-running
rituals also appear here when active.  These are toggle rites, such as
Verdant Refrain, that remain active until you end them with
|CKBritual stop <name>|000.

The moon currents are strongest when their moon is visible and weakest
during the new moon.  Tellurian is strongest in living earth and your
Sacred Grove.

When Dailos, Markas, and Tekal are all new at once, all three lunar
currents are starved together.  Use |CKBmoonless drawing|000 during
that rare dark to restore enough Daloan, Marken, and Tekali nwyfre to
keep working.

|GKB-- Conjunctions ----------------------------------------------|000

When two or more moons are full in the night sky, nwyfre enters a
rare conjunction.  'nwyfre' shows the current conjunction line.
Most nights this says 'none'.  During a two-moon conjunction,
Twin-Moon Pact can bind the aligned lunar currents together.

When Dailos, Markas, and Tekal are all full at once, an ancient
Sacred Grove can work Triple Confluence Calling.  This is an
endgame ritual window, not a daily tool.

New druids should read |CKBdhelp beginner|000 for the first useful
sequence: check nwyfre, learn an invocation, gather profession
materials, plant a grove, learn a ritual, perform it, then cast.
